verses.roman:
dharite dharite gharera bharila eka koṇa
śata-janera bhakṣya yata haila sañcayana

synonyms: dharite dharite—keeping and keeping; gharera—of the room; bharila—filled up; eka koṇa—one corner; śata-janera—of one hundred people; bhakṣya—sufficient for feeding; yata—all; haila—there was; sañcayana—accumulation.
translation: Govinda kept accumulating the food, and soon it filled a corner of the room. There was quite enough to feed at least a hundred people.
